Description: Downsizing my guitar collection. This is a stunning looking Guitar and more importantly it's plays like a dream! :) This is a rare Fender Telecaster - this version (Version1) was only made for 2 years. Jonny Greenwood has a couple of these and I believe has used one on every Radiohead album. Fender Telecaster Plus DELUXE This guitar was made at the Corona Plant (Fender), USA.It will ship in the case shown in the pics. It has 3 'nicks' - see pics, Frets have hardly any wear.The Plus Deluxe is a fairly rare model (from the 1989-91 run) that features a Two Point Tremelo, Wilkinson Nut, Original Lace Sensor Pickups, TBX Tone Control, Hipshot Tremsetter, and Locking Tuners. SPECS:Nut Width: 1.66"1st Fret: 0.76"12th Fret: 0.83"Neck Type: "C" ShapeFinger Board: MaplePickups: This Telecaster Plus (Version One) comes equipped with Lace Sensor pickups; "Dually Red-Red" in the bridge position and "Blue" in the neck position.
